        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-10T02:22:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what if content type is not text? in L482 we check both contentType and data.options.format. Why this check is inconsistent?",
      "revId": "cdb475567c9104d1fe4bd16993929176292054c0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c476089c_5fb13b44",
        "filename": "logdog/appengine/coordinator/flex/logs/http.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 487,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-15T19:42:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. We\u0027ll still render the HTML header if it is not text, but the user asks for HTML (ie if it\u0027s binary or datagram, ?format\u003dhtml essentially means \"please pretty print my data\").\n2. Datagrams aren\u0027t supported ATM (check done in L285), so at the moment the L482 check is actually useless.  But even if we did support datagrams, I think this is correct, because if the raw format is requested, we don\u0027t write the HTML header, and if HTML format is requested, we always write the HTML header.",
      "parentUuid": "45e34cef_7c349a66",
      "revId": "cdb475567c9104d1fe4bd16993929176292054c0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    }
